<h2 id="50">2. Registering with Skrill</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Open a <a href="https://content.skrill.com/en/ecommerce-solutions/plentymarkets/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">seller account</a> on Skrill first. For business registration, click the <strong>Sign up now</strong> button. Follow the next steps to complete the registration process. In one of these steps, you will be asked to enter a <strong>secret word</strong> that is used to encrypt payments. You need this secret word to set up the access data in plentymarkets. This secret word should be different from your login password and may contain no more than 10 characters. The secret word may only consist of lower-case letters and numbers. It may not contain special characters.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Familiarise yourself with the <strong>history</strong> section in your Skrill account as well. Later, you will be able to download your transaction history as an Excel table here and process it as needed.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="60">3. Setting up Skrill for Callisto</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Skrill uses a two-stage security concept for activating accounts. Stage 1 is the verification of your email address. Stage 2 is the verification of your personal data. Proceed as described below to set up the interface to Skrill for your Callisto online store in plentymarkets.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting up the Skrill interface:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Orders » Payment » Methods</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Place a check mark next to the setting <strong>Also show inactive</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the folder <strong>International</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Skrill</strong>.<br>
→ The <strong>Interface</strong> tab will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the email address that you received from Skrill.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the secret word that you received from Skrill.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="70">4. Activating payment methods</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Set up and activate the Skrill <a href="/en/payment/managing-payment-methods#20">payment methods</a> in the <strong>Settings</strong> tab of the payment methods. In addition, check the settings for <strong>Permitted payment methods</strong> in the <a href="/en/payment/managing-payment-methods#30">customer classes</a> and for <strong>Blocked payment methods</strong> in the <a href="/en/fulfilment/preparing-the-shipment#1000">shipping profiles</a>.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Changing the payment method after an order was placed</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>It is not possible for a customer to change the <strong>payment method</strong> within the <strong>my account</strong> area of the online store after they have placed an order and before they have received a confirmation of payment. A corresponding note is displayed in the <strong>my account</strong> area. If the payment was denied, the payment method can be changed.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
